        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 4:51PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 450 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Laingsburg, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Owosso, Durand, Perry, Laingsburg, Corunna, Morrice, Byron, Bancroft,
Lennon, Henderson, Bennington, Vernon, Juddville, and Carland.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
